{
  "stem": "5275.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A somewhat traumatic event I remember also was when it was raining.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the Germans were using a number of the Jewish factories in the ghetto to make uniforms for the soldiers.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And one day, I was walking down what was known as Leshno Street, one of the main streets.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And a big German truck drove by and stopped in front of the factory.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they started unloading bales of material for the uniforms.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And one of the Germans caught me and put this big bale on my [NON-ENGLISH] on my shoulder, and asked me to carry it to the factory, which was about, oh, I would say, at least 150 feet away.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was raining.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There were puddles of water.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "He took out a gun, and he told me [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] [DRINKS WATER] that-- [EMOTIONAL] [SIGHS] [PAUSES FOR 14 SECONDS] he told me that, if I was going to drop the bale, he was going to shoot me.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And as I was carrying this thing, I really thought that I was going to drop it.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I just-- it was too heavy for me, but I somehow made it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[EMOTIONAL] [SIGHS] Another time, my mother, of course, who was very much involved with art, theater, and so on-- there was a Jewish theater in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And she took me to a play, to see a play with famous Jewish actors.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[COUGHS] In the middle of the play, the Germans surrounded the theater and took everybody in the courtyard, put them against the wall.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We were all against the wall.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "They took the guns and pointed at us and started shooting.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And they shoot right above our heads.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And then they laughed.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "[EMOTIONAL] My mother also always impressed me the importance of learning, education.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
